In my moments of deep thought 💭 I think of what I dreamt of as a little girl. 

Its really not what the vision is or was back then… it is what the vision DOES FOR OTHERS. Am I right ? I love 💗 helping young people and even my younger clients think of their vision & helping them connect to people that can help them. 

A vision is not just a picture of what could be; it is an appeal to our BETTER selves, a call to become something more.

Tens of thousands of books and reading rooms nationwide and growing … @andre_reed83 & @theresa_vpr are committed to helping @bgca_clubs & on a mission ! They have remodeled 16 reading rooms, visited 64 + clubs in 32 states using athletes to help make reading cool again. 📚

For more information contact @sdtammyn . It’s the best ⛳️ outing ever. Too much is given much is expected.

Feeling this … you ? 
🧐🫶🏻 We become the journey . I had lots of let downs. Heart break. Disappointments. I kept going when people said stop. CHANGE DIRECTIONS. There’s hope in the pivot & shift… welcome the direction changes. There WILL be doors to open that will shine ✨ your light even BRIGHTER ! You will find a different path where people accept you and see your worth. There is a journey that is a better fit for your purpose. ☝🏻 #feelingsentimental #growGIRL #bekind #inspirepeople

Girls inspiring girls ! Some of our new young readers x @theresa_vpr after her presentation . Although our program is focused on PRO athletes “making reading cool” Theresa is and has been the MC of all our READ WITH REED rally’s for the last 5 years. She entertains the kids and has a true passion for inspiring these club kids in underserved communities. She helps break down for the youth that reading is a resource + tool that will help them go after a GREAT FUTURE no matter where they come from!✨ Looks like these little @bgcarizona were inspired by this amazing event in PHX for Super Bowl . #reading #nflplayers #girlswholift

Who is going to the game Saturday? ⚾️🤞🏻So stoked to speak to young aspiring #SDSU college students in the @sbisdsu // @sdsuwomeninsports program at PETCO park. 

Honestly, one of my greater purposes is to give more to young people in this space! Here to represent people that THOUGHT IS SHOULD CHANGE CAREERS and take an easier “more stable” path. ✔️ Here to represent WOMAN owning & CO OWNING COMPANIES! ✔️HERE to represent WOMAN working for MALE & FEMALE PROS. ✔️HERE TO show them that although it’s competitive, there are kind , go getter people that will give them a chance! 

Finding your dream job isn’t for the faint hearted, especially in the sports space where there’s lots of applications, and not as many jobs. Things take time. Go after your dream job. Your timeline isn’t like everyone else’s. You are one person away from your next opportunity. YOU CAN WORK HARD, BE A BOSS & BE NICE TOO ! LFG SD . See you Saturday.

ABOUT THE NAME . Honored to launch the SAN DIEGO MOJO 🏐 @sandiegomojovb this week with @kerrileewalsh at the @theultimateskybox ! 

Here is the meaning behind our newest team …

🪄 MOJO NAME = The best teams in the world have this magical, undeniable essence about them. The best athletes and performers in the world have the same - we intend to embody that essence, that magic, that MOJO. 

 🦅 OSPREY MASCOT = The osprey, renowned for its strength, resilience, and mastery of the skies, has become an emblem of inspiration. It’s remarkable journey of survival mirrors the determination, grace, and courage that will be exhibited by the women of the San Diego Mojo in their pursuit of excellence. 

🌅 With this new horizon, the Mojo’s aspirations and ambitions soar as high as the osprey in pursuit of their passions without limitations. A once-endangered species, the osprey fought its way through and now has returned to San Diego after being absent for a long time.
